<text>Inger and Lasse Sandberg were Swedish authors of children&#x27;s books. The stories were written by Inger and illustrated by her husband Lasse. They have created many characters, including &quot;The Little Ghost Godfrey&quot; (Sw: &quot;Lilla SpÃ¶ket Laban&quot;) and &quot;Little Anna and the Tall Uncle&quot;. Inger received the Nils Holgersson Plaque. They were joint recipients of Expressens Heffaklump in 1969.

